snippet.title: Roly Poly World: Learning Game for Kids | LeapFrog
snippet.description:
Have your child join the Roly Poly family on a rollicking trip to the Roly Poly World amusement park. In this fun-filled learning game, they'll explore 20 levels across four unique lands: Wild West, Candy Castle, Pirate Bug Cove and the Haunted Ghost Hotel. They can tilt and turn their LeapPad to collect gold coins, find hidden gems, herd cowbugs and battle bandit and pirate bugs. They'll identify letters and use spelling skills to build words, then roll to the correct answers to earn a shiny golden ticket from Papa Roly at the Super Speller's Ticket Booth. They can even play with a friend using peer-to-peer-enabled multiplayer on LeapPad Ultra and work together to collect all the gems!

Sound doesn't work?
Try Increasing the volume and check that your device is not set to "Mute". The Mute button is located next to the volume buttons on the side of the device.

Still no sound?
On the iPad it's possible that your side switch is set to lock screen rotation. In this case you can control sound volume by:
- Double tap the home button
- Swipe the lower bar from left to right
- Tap the speaker icon to the far left
- It should show "Mute Off" below the play button
